    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-07-24T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-07-24T20:00:00-05:00" n="198"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d198">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7–2547: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ward</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-07-25T10:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 25, 1947—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 28—5:47 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>178. Cheng Tung-kuo, Acting Commander NECC, informed Colonel Barrett,<note n="36"
                        xml:id="d198fn1">David D. Barrett.</note> A[ssistant] Military Attaché, July
                    25: <pb facs="0254" n="244" xml:id="pg_244"/>
                    <list>
                        <label>(1)</label>
                        <item>Nationals in Manchuria unable effect counteroffensive without
                            reinforcements provided existing acute shortage ammunition and equipment
                            relieved.</item>
                        <label>(2)</label>
                        <item>No independent Korean units operating with Communists NE. Considerable
                            numbers Korean with Communist armies but are integrated into regular
                            Chinese units.</item>
                        <label>(3)</label>
                        <item>Only few very old pieces equipment captured from Communists by
                            Nationals. Does not believe Russia supplying Communists Soviet equipment
                            which latter would give away Soviet policy to United States. Are
                            supplying Communists Jap equipment only.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ward</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
